These are the necessary steps to prepare an Ubuntu 12.04 LTS 
machine for frontend development

1.) Install add-apt-repository command:

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install python-software-properties git

2.) Install nodejs repository

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:chris-lea/node.js

3.) Install nodejs + npm

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install nodejs

4.) Install global dependencies

npm config set tmp=/tmp
sudo npm -g install yo bower grunt-cli

5.) Check out repository

git clone <user>@masterhoschi.dyndns.org:/var/repos/frontend

6.) Install local dependencies

cd frontend
npm install

6.1) Re install bower dependencies (optional)

please note: all bower dependencies are checked into the repository, the main
reason easier development - now it's possible to simply use apache to serve the 
site without installing any build tools. In case the bower dependencies should
re installed, delete the folder and then install the deps.

rm -fr app/bower_components
bower install

7.) Start frontend

grunt serve

The application will now run on 127.0.0.1:9000

